            other purposes or uses. All GIS data sets are provided "as is" with no warranty. All
            users should consult public primary information sources, such as recorded deeds and
            plats, to verify the accuracy of the data provided. It is the user's responsibility to
            verify any information derived from the GIS data before making any decisions or taking
            any action based on the information. Use of all GIS data and map services provided by
            the City of Asheville are covered by this disclaimer.
          </div>
          <div class='modal-footer'>
            <button
              id='acceptDisclaimer'
              type='submit'
              class='btn btn-secondary'
              data-dismiss='modal'
              autofocus
            >Accept</button>
          </div>
        </form>
      </div>
    </div>

